<h2 id="controls">Controls</h2>
<p>Arrow Arena keeps controls simple but the execution challenging. Here's everything you need to know:</p>

<table>
<thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>Key</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Move</td><td>WASD or Arrow Keys</td></tr>
<tr><td>Aim</td><td>Mouse</td></tr>
<tr><td>Normal Attack / Charge Shot</td><td>Left Mouse Button (tap or hold)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Special Attack</td><td>Right Mouse Button</td></tr>
<tr><td>Select Upgrade Skills</td><td>Numpad 1-3</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>The twin-stick setup (WASD to move, mouse to aim) means you can strafe while shooting in a different direction. Master this and you'll dodge arrows while still landing hits.</p>

<h2 id="combat">Combat Mechanics</h2>

<div class="tip-title">🏹 Normal Attacks</div>
<p>A quick tap of the left mouse button fires a standard arrow instantly. These are fast, reliable, and perfect for close-range encounters or when you need to get damage out quickly. Normal arrows deal moderate damage but have the advantage of zero commitment — fire and move immediately.</p>

<div class="tip-title">⚡ Charged Shots</div>
<p>Hold the left mouse button and your archer charges a more powerful arrow. The longer you hold, the more damage it deals. A fully charged shot can eliminate opponents in one hit if they're low on health. But here's the thing: you move slower while charging, and you're vulnerable to flanking. Timing is everything — release at the right moment when your target is predictable.</p>

<div class="tip-title">🎯 Special Attacks</div>
<p>Right-click for a special attack that deals heavy damage. These are most effective when opponents are trapped against walls or distracted fighting someone else. Save them for high-value moments rather than spamming.</p>

