</figure>

<h2 id="upgrades">Skill Upgrade System</h2>
<p>Every time you level up (from kills or survival time), you get to choose from random skill upgrades. This is where Arrow Arena really shines — different upgrade paths create completely different playstyles.</p>

<div class="tip-title">📈 Upgrade Categories</div>
<table>
<thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Effect</th><th>Playstyle</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Bouncing Arrows</td><td>Arrows ricochet off walls</td><td>Tactical area control</td></tr>
<tr><td>Multi-Shot</td><td>Fire multiple arrows at once</td><td>Aggressive close-range</td></tr>
<tr><td>Explosive Arrows</td><td>Area-of-effect damage on impact</td><td>Crowd control</td></tr>
<tr><td>Mobility Boosts</td><td>Increased movement speed</td><td>Hit-and-run sniper</td></tr>
<tr><td>Damage Multipliers</td><td>Higher base arrow damage</td><td>One-shot potential</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>Trust me, the second upgrade level matters more than the first. That's when your build starts becoming truly dangerous. Some combinations turn you into a walking turret, others make you nearly untouchable.</p>

<h2 id="tips">Tips &amp; Strategies</h2>

<div class="tip-title">🏃 Keep Moving Constantly</div>
<p>Standing still in Arrow Arena is a death sentence. Arrows fly from every direction, and a stationary target is an easy target. Strafe while aiming, use obstacles for cover, and never commit to a position for too long.</p>

<div class="tip-title">🎯 Use Corners for Bouncing Arrows</div>
<p>If you've picked up the bouncing arrows upgrade (or even without it), use arena walls to your advantage. Shoot at angles where enemies can't see you coming. This is especially effective in tight corridors and around obstacles.</p>

<div class="tip-title">⚡ Charge Shots Wisely</div>
<p>Charged shots deal massive damage but leave you vulnerable. Only charge when you have cover or your target is predictable (like when they're fighting someone else). If you feel exposed, switch to quick normal shots instead.</p>

<div class="tip-title">💎 Farm Crystals Early</div>
<p>Don't rush into combat at the start of a match. Spend the first few seconds collecting crystals and gaining XP to level up. A higher-level archer with good upgrades dominates early-game fighters who skipped farming.</p>

<div class="tip-title">🏆 Steal Loot from Fights</div>
<p>When two players battle, the winner drops a pile of crystals. Wait for the dust to settle, then swoop in and grab the loot. It's safer than initiating fights and still gets you leveling up quickly.</p>

<div class="tip-title">👀 Watch Every Angle</div>
<p>Don't hyper-focus on one opponent. In a multiplayer arena, someone's always flanking. Keep your awareness up and be ready to disengage if you sense danger from another direction.</p>

<div class="tip-title">🎮 Save Special Attacks</div>
<p>Special attacks hit hard but have cooldown implications. Use them when opponents are trapped, distracted, or low on health. Wasting them on full-health targets at range is throwing away your advantage.</p>

